The paper discusses data processing techniques for big data, specifically focusing on constructing approximate equi-depth histograms. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, since the paper primarily focuses on data processing and storage, cs.DB and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions query optimization, which is a common topic in cs.DB.
